  "market_context": "Friday, August 4, 2023, post-Thursday sweep of previous day low. ES showed relative strength (↑) while NQ showed relative weakness (↓) per ES/NQ ratio chart. Monthly FVG on NQ and daily FVG on ES were key HTF POIs.",
  "key_observation": "NQ failed to reach morning highs while ES swept its FVG CE and reversed; this SMT divergence signaled bearish NQ into monthly FVG, then a long entry at FVG CE after displacement lower.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst observed ES/NQ ratio showing ES ↑ and NQ ↓, indicating relative weakness in NQ versus ES on higher time frames.",
    "Step 2: Identified monthly fair value gap (FVG) on NQ and daily FVG on ES, with consequent encroachment (CE) marked as key POIs.",
    "Step 3: Noted NQ barely reached up into the monthly FVG before an aggressive displacement candle lower, while ES swept the CE of its daily FVG and reversed.",
    "Step 4: Recognized SMT at the low displacement: NQ made a lower low while ES made a higher low, confirming relative weakness and setting up a short into the monthly FVG.",
    "Step 5: After the displacement lower, observed NQ retesting the FVG CE with an up-close candle that closed below the mean threshold, triggering a long setup at the CE zone."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long trade taken at FVG CE after SMT confirmation; price expanded toward morning highs as ES remained strong and NQ reversed.",
  "lessons": "Relative strength via ES/NQ ratio identifies which asset to trade; FVG CE serves as high-probability OTE zone when paired with SMT and displacement; mean threshold validates entry validity.",
